<div class='row'>
  <div id="news" class='col-lg-9'>
    <h1 class="text-center">Welcome to MetWork </h1>
    <h2 class="text-center"><i>a web server for natural products anticipation</i></h2>
    <p class="text-center"><i>Currently running beta version {{version}}</i></p>
    <h3 class="text-center">Latest News</h3>
    {{#latest-news
      date="29th May 2019"
      title="New adducts features"}}
      Those new features have been introduced :
      <ul>
        <li> Handling other adducts ([M+], [M+Na]+, [M+K]+ and [M+NH4]+ for in silico fragmentation</li>
        <li> Automated recognition of adducts type from raw data</li>
        </ul>
    {{/latest-news }}
    {{#latest-news
      date="15th May 2019"
      title="MetWork Paper online"}}
      The MetWork paper published in the Bioinformatics journal is available on
      <a href="https://academic.oup.com/bioinformatics/article/35/10/1795/5116145" target="_blank">
      this link</a>.
    {{/latest-news }}

    {{#latest-news
      date="19th October 2018"
      title="Reaction edition online"}}
      The beta version 0.3 is online with the possibility to edit new reaction online.
      For compatbility reason, previous reaction have been made obsolete and new ones will be created.
    {{/latest-news }}

    {{#latest-news
      date="20th September 2018"
      title="Networks visualizations available !"}}

      You can see molecular network of your frag sample data and metabolization network for finished project.
      <br />
      Click on graph nodes to display info.
     <img class="card-img-bottom mt-2 border" src="/assets/images/metabolization_network_screenshot.png"
     alt="metabolization_network_screenshot">
     <img class="card-img-bottom mt-1 border" src="/assets/images/molecular_network_screenshot.png"
     alt="molecular_network_screenshot">
    {{/latest-news }}

    {{#latest-news
      date="10th August 2018"
      title="New beta version"}}

      Those new features have been introduced :
      <ul>
        <li> Improvement of cosine score calculation with Metgem algorithm ( https://github.com/metgem/metgem ) </li>
        <li> Availability to directly import GNPS .tsv annotation files </li>
        <li> Clone achieved project </li>
        <li> Download all molecules generated </li>
        <li> New design to select reactions and ion annotations on a project </li>
        <li>  Speed improvement to import fragmentation data </li>
      </ul>
    {{/latest-news }}

    {{#latest-news
      date="1st August 2018"
      title="Source code on GitHub"}}

      The code of MetWork is available on GitHub :
      <a href="https://github.com/metwork-project" target="_blank"> https://github.com/metwork-project </a>
    {{/latest-news }}
  </div>
  <div class='col-lg-3'>
    <div id="api-status" >
      <div class="card border-{{statusColor}}">
        <div class="card-header text-white bg-{{statusColor}} text-center">
          API Status
        </div>
        {{#if apiStatus.loading}}
          <div class="card-body text-primary text-center">
              {{ember-spinner }}
          </div>
        {{else if apiStatus.status.available}}
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title text-success mb-0 text-center">Service available</h5>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush bg-danger">
            <li class="list-group-item">Molecules generated : {{apiStatus.status.molecules_count}}</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Projects achieved : {{apiStatus.status.achieved_projects_count}}</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Projects running : {{apiStatus.status.running_projects_count}}</li>
          </ul>
        {{else}}
          <div class="card-body text-danger text-center">
            <h5 class="card-title">Under maintenance</h5>
            Service is currently unavailable and will be back soon.
          </div>
        {{/if}}

      </div>
      <div class="card border-primary mt-2">
        <div class="card-header text-white bg-primary text-center">
          MetWork Main Paper
        </div>
        <div class="card-body text-primary text-center">
